cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on using robot kinematic data for skill assessment in robotic surgery training. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper discusses using visual data (robot kinematic data) for skill assessment. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are relevant categories as the paper proposes a machine learning-based approach for automated skill assessment. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the potential for real-time score feedback in RMIS training, which involves interaction between humans and computers.
